# Built binaries
/comrade
/comrade.exe
/dist/

# CI-generated SBOMs (release.yml's anchore/sbom-action step writes its
# output to $RUNNER_TEMP, outside this workspace, specifically to avoid
# this — but this pattern is a belt-and-suspenders guard: if that step's
# output-file ever gets pointed back into the repo, an untracked SBOM
# file here would make `git status --porcelain` report "dirty" and fail
# goreleaser's git-state check before the release even starts, exactly
# as happened in the v0.1.0 tag's first (failed) run.
/sbom-*.cdx.json

# Coverage
*.out
coverage.txt
coverage.html

# OS cruft
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Editor/IDE
.vscode/
.idea/

# Local scratch state (never versioned)
.remember/
.claude/
